[5] CDC guidelines for gauging risk of Ebola transmission & patient management
Date: 25 Nov 2014
Source: CDC [edited]
http://www.cdc.gov/vhf/ebola/hcp/international/determining-risk.html


(1) For Community and Healthcare Settings in West Africa: Determining Risk of Ebola Transmission
---------------------------------------
Since the discovery of Ebola virus, there have been Ebola infections among healthcare workers in almost every outbreak. Protecting healthcare workers from Ebola infection and improving infection control are critical elements to provide reliable health care and stop the epidemic... - more

***
For General Healthcare Settings in West Africa: Managing Ebola Patients, Their Families, and the Community Safely and Compassionately
---------------------------------------
Date: 25 Nov 2014
Source: CDC [edited]
http://www.cdc.gov/vhf/ebola/hcp/international/manage-safely-and-compassionately.html


(2) Management of Suspected Ebola Patients in General Healthcare Settings (Non-Ebola Treatment Units)
----------------------------------------
- Safely isolate and manage patients with suspected Ebola cases.
- Alert public health authorities about a suspected Ebola case.
- Educate family and the community about what they can do to stay healthy.
- All patients coming to the healthcare facility must be assessed for Ebola based on the screening flowchart.
- Any patient suspected of having Ebola should be immediately directed to the isolation area. Proper public health authorities should be immediately notified.
- Any patient suspected of having Ebola needs to be isolated while waiting for the ambulance to pick them up. If more than one patient is isolated in your facility, keep them at least one meter apart... - more

