[6] Sierra Leone: ASEOWA takes charge of ETC
Date: 24 Nov 2014
Source: Union Africaine [edited]
http://www.au.int/fr/content/aseowa-takes-charge-ebola-treatment-centre-bombali-district-sierra-leone


The African Union Support to the Ebola Outbreak in West Africa, ASEOWA, in Sierra Leone has received the go-ahead for the management of the newly completed Ebola Treatment Centre (ETC) in Magbenteh, Bombali District of Sierra Leone. The coordination of the ETC will be in partnership with the Ministry of Health of Sierra Leone. President Ernest Bai Koroma, while commissioning the treatment centre on Sun 16 Nov 2014, commended the efforts of the African Union in providing medical personnel in fighting against the Ebola virus disease.

The Magbenteh treatment centre, with a bed space capacity of 100 was scheduled to receive its 1st 6 Ebola patients on Mon 24 Nov 2014. The treatment centre is expected to ease the backlog of sick patients at the Arab, Paramedic, Government and Kamakwe holding centres in Bombali District, where Ebola patients were held pending their transfer to Kailahun, a neighboring district, for treatment... - more

