[7] West Africa: EU Offloads Anti-Ebola Cargo
Date: 25 Nov 2014
Source: New Dawn [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201411250921.html


The Dutch government and 8 other European Union member states have presented a [sea-borne] cargo of anti-Ebola materials valued at 3.6 million Euros [USD 4.5 million], including 2 fully-equipped ambulances, a laboratory, jumper delivery beds [sic: can't discover what they are, probably obstetric - Mod.JW], body beds, protective suits, goggles, respiratory masks, and rubber boots, among others...

The Netherlands envoy told President Sirleaf that upon discharging the ship, it was returning to Europe to pick up a 2nd cargo of anti-Ebola items for the 3 countries to be back in Monrovia around the Christmas season... - more

