******
[8] Sierra Leone: burial workers strike
Date: Tue 25 Nov 2014
Source: BBC edited [edited]
http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-30191938


Burial workers in the Sierra Leonean city of Kenema have dumped bodies in public in protest at non-payment of allowances for October and November 2014 handling of Ebola victims.

The workers, who went on strike over the issue, left 15 bodies abandoned at the city's main hospital. One body was reportedly left by the office of the hospital manager and 2 others by the hospital entrance. The bodies have now been taken away, but the workers have refused to end their strike. It has been reported that the striking workers have now been sacked. There has been no public comment by the hospital's management or the Sierra Leonean health ministry.

The burial workers' industrial action came 2 weeks after health workers went on strike for similar reasons at a clinic near Bo, the only facility in southern Sierra Leone treating Ebola victims... more

